al fortress situated in the eastern Scottish Borders of which little remains. The site is protected as a scheduled monument.', 'Castle of Medinaceli | The Castle of Medinaceli is a medieval fortress in Medinaceli, Soria. It was built in the 9th century and rebuilt in the 15th century. Almanzor died here in 1002.', 'Fortress of Ulm | The fortress of Ulm ("Bundesfestung Ulm") was one of five federal fortresses of the German Confederation around the cities of Ulm and Neu-Ulm. With its 9 km polygonal main circumvallation Ulm had the biggest fortress in Germany in the 19th century and it is still one of the biggest in Europe.'], 'question': 'Buncle is a name derived from which medieval fortress?', 'reasoning': 'The question mentions "Buncle" which is derived from a medieval fortress, so we need to find the context of that fortress.', 'search_query': '"Buncle medieval fortress"\n"Buncle origin medieval fortress"\n"Medieval fortress name Buncle"'}) (input_keys=None), Example({'question': 'What song did John Lennon write in his house at Menlove Avenue that lead The Beatles to a commercial breakthrough prior to the release of "She Loves You"?', 'answer': '"Please Please Me"'}) (input_keys={'question'})]

